    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-cou1-cpb-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-lab-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed the required levels for Model Risk Level 2. The six non-assessed factors are appropriately scoped out per ASME V&V 40 Table 4 guidance for MRL 2. The hemolysis power-law model parameterisation relies on the consolidated re-calibration dataset described in the reference indexed via referencesIdentifier (doi:10.1016/j.ymeth.2024.03.003), which provides updated coefficients validated across multiple pump geometries. Grid convergence is demonstrated, validation activities are relevant to the COU, and the RH < 1 criterion is satisfied across all worst-case operating conditions. The credibility package is accepted for regulatory submission supporting the Class II CPB device 510(k) pathway.",
